# SME — Jigg Runtime

Authority: Store mutation rules, runtime state shape, Plate behavior, interaction lifecycle.

Invoke when a story involves:
- deciding what lives in the store vs pipeline
- piece state mutations (position, stage, rotation, cluster)
- store ↔ Plate reactivity
- ARIA behavior, focus management, keyboard navigation
- anything that changes during active play

---

## Runtime = Everything Live

The runtime system is everything that happens while the app is running:
- Store holds mutable state
- Plate reacts to it
- `plate/aria/runtime/` owns all interaction behavior

The boundary that matters:
> "Is this derivation or live behavior?"
> Derivation → pipeline. Live → runtime.

---

## Accessibility in Runtime

Accessibility is not a module — it is distributed:

| Layer | Location | What |
|---|---|---|
| User intent | Store (`puzzleStore.a11y`) | contrast mode, reduce motion, focus mode |
| Derivation | `cook/deriveA11ySpec.ts` | produces `RenderSpec.a11y` — pipeline concern |
| Runtime behavior | `plate/aria/runtime/` | focus, keyboard, ARIA, announcements |

`plate/aria/runtime/` is the ONLY place runtime a11y behavior lives.
There is no `src/a11y/` folder.

---

## What Lives in the Store

```ts
import type { JiggAssembly, PieceState } from '@jigg-spec/types'
```

| Concern | Store? |
|---|---|
| Piece positions, stage, rotation | ✅ `JiggAssembly.pieces` |
| Cluster membership | ✅ `PieceState.clusterId` |
| Play time | ✅ `JiggAssembly.playTimeSeconds` |
| Camera / viewport | ✅ `JiggAssembly.view` |
| User a11y prefs (contrast, motion) | ✅ passed as `A11yPrefs` snapshot to Cook |
| Focus mode, selection | ✅ runtime only — consumed by `plate/aria/runtime/` |
| Cut geometry / piece definitions | ❌ `JiggDissection` |
| Board color, contrast rules | ❌ `RenderSpec.a11y` |

---

## Store ↔ Plate

```
User interaction → Store mutation → Plate reacts → PixiJS + ARIA update
```

Plate reads from Store during runtime loop. Never writes derived structure back.

---

## Piece State Invariants

- `placed === true` → `clusterId` absent (enforce immediately)
- `STAGE_BENCH` → `pos` absent, `clusterId` absent
- Non-bench → `pos` present
- `rot` always a valid cardinal: `{0, 90, 180, 270}`
- No piece transitions back to `STAGE_BENCH`
- Ghost tray: missing `stageId` → move piece to `STAGE_TABLE`

---

## Cluster Rules

- `clusterId` generated at snap time (NanoID 8)
- Merge: larger group survives; tie → lower `PieceDefinition.index` wins
- Surviving origin piece stays fixed in world space
- Absorbed pieces recompute `pos` relative to origin
- Incompatible rotations → merge rejected
- No cluster breakup

---

## ARIA Structure

```
#app
  [bench]   role="application" — inert when table mode active
  [table]   role="application" — inert when bench mode active
  [live]    aria-live — announcements only
[app shell] siblings of #app — never inside PixiJS region
```

`role="application"` suppresses AT shortcut keys — app owns all key events.

